## 🚀 What is TOBY MK1?

TOBY MK1 runs TOBYOS V.1 PRO - an offline tactical operating system on ESP32.

Philosophy: Pocket computer. No internet. No cloud. No tracking. Just hardware.

Hardware Status: Planning phase. Physical assembly scheduled for December/2026.

## ⚙️ Hardware - Real BOM

COMPONENT - MODEL - FUNCTION IN TOBYOS:
- MCU: ESP32-WROOM-32 - Runs TOBYOS + WiFi + BT + SPI
- Display: 2.8" TFT Touch ST7789 - 240x320 Touch UI + Virtual Keyboard
- Storage: MicroSD Slot - Built into TFT module. TOBYOS file system
- GPS: NEO-6M - GPS App - Coordinates + GPX logging
- Radio: CC1101 433MHz - RF Scanner App - Detects 433MHz signals
- IR: IR LED + Receiver - IR App - Clone/control TV, AC remotes
- Power: 18650 3.7V - Main battery
- Button: 1x Power - ON/OFF ONLY. Does NOT control apps

NOT INCLUDED: RTC, FM radio, calculator, physical keypad.
Estimated Cost: $50 - $65 USD

## 📱 TOBYOS V.1 PRO - 8 Independent Apps

All apps work standalone via touchscreen. No app requires another.

APP LIST:
1. Settings - Adjust brightness, sound, touch calibration, WiFi AP password
2. Wi-Fi - Scan 2.4GHz networks, AP mode, packet info
3. Bluetooth - BLE scanner, detect beacons, RSSI
4. IR Remote - Record/send IR codes. Control TV, AC
5. RF Scanner - CC1101 433MHz. Detect remotes, sensors. NOT a messenger
6. GPS Tracker - Lat/Lon/Alt/Speed. Save GPX logs to SD
7. SCFTOS - SiteControlForTobyOS - Optional remote control via phone
8. Bootloader - Update TOBYOS firmware via SD card or WiFi OTA

SCFTOS is OPTIONAL. Device works 100% without phone. SCFTOS just lets you control/download via browser.

## 📖 USER MANUAL - How to Use TOBY MK1

### **1. Power On/Off**
- TURN ON: Long press power button 2 seconds → TOBYOS boots
- TURN OFF: Long press power button 3 seconds → Shutdown
- Power button DOES NOTHING ELSE. All control is via touchscreen.

### **2. Main Screen - App Menu**

After power on, you see the main screen with 8 buttons arranged like this:
Row 1: [Config] [Wi-Fi]
Row 2: [Bluetooth] [IR]
Row 3: [Radio] [GPS]
Row 4: [SCFTOS] [Bootloader]

At the top of the screen it shows: TOBYOS V.1 PRO + Time + Battery icon
At the bottom it shows: Touch to open | SD: 3.1GB Free

Tap any button to open the app.

### **3. Using Settings App**

1. Tap the [Config] button on main screen
2. Settings screen opens showing:
   - Brightness: Slider from 0% to 100%
   - Sound: Button showing ON or OFF
   - Touch: Button CALIBRATE
   - WiFi AP Name: TOBY-MK1
   - AP Password: toby12345 + Button CHANGE
   - Language: EN-US
   - Button at bottom
3. Adjust what you want by tapping sliders or buttons
4. Tap the button to apply changes
5. Tap [< Back] to return to main menu

### **4. Using GPS Tracker App**

1. Tap the **[GPS]** button on main screen
2. GPS screen opens showing "SEARCHING SATELLITES"
3. Wait 30 seconds for satellite lock
4. When locked, screen shows:
   - Status: LOCKED
   - LAT: -5.794478 S
   - LON: -35.211001 W
   - ALT: 52m
   - SPD: 0 km/h
   - SAT: 8
   - Accuracy: ±6m
   - Buttons: [UPDATE] [SAVE LOG]
5. Tap **[SAVE LOG]** → Saves coordinates to /GPS/2026-06-27.gpx on SD card
6. Tap **[< Back]** to return to main menu

### **5. Using RF Scanner - CC1101**

1. Tap the **[Radio]** button on main screen
2. RF Scanner screen opens showing:
   - Frequency: 433.920 MHz + Button [SET]
   - Signal bar: Shows signal strength
   - Text: Waiting for signal...
   - Buttons: [LISTEN]
3. When it detects a remote control signal, screen shows:
   - Signal: -65 dBm
   - LAST SIGNAL: 00:58:41 F0A1B2C3
   - Type: Remote Control
4. Tap **** → Saves data to /RF/scan.log on SD card
5. THIS IS NOT A CHAT. It detects garage remotes, sensors, etc.
6. Tap **[< Back]** to return to main menu

### **6. Using Wi-Fi Scanner**

1. Tap the **[Wi-Fi]** button on main screen
2. WiFi list appears on screen:
   - VIVOFIBRA -45dBm Channel 6 WPA2
   - Claro_2.4G -68dBm Channel 11 WPA2
   - Neighbor -82dBm Channel 1 OPEN
3. Tap any network to see MAC and Vendor details
4. Tap button **[AP MODE]** → Creates "TOBY-MK1" network for SCFTOS
5. Tap button **[SAVE LIST]** to save networks to SD
6. Tap **[< Back]** to return to main menu

### **7. Using Bluetooth Scanner**

1. Tap the **[Bluetooth]** button on main screen
2. BLE device list appears:
   - MiBand7 -59dBm Wearable
   - Tile-AB12 -71dBm Tracker
   - Unknown -85dBm Beacon
3. Tap any device to see details
4. Tap button **** to save to SD
5. Tap **[< Back]** to return to main menu

### **8. Using IR Remote**

1. Tap the **[IR]** button on main screen
2. IR screen opens showing:
   - Mode: Buttons [SEND] [LEARN]
   - Last code: ---
   - Protocol: ---
   - Saved profiles: TV_POWER | AR_SAMSUNG
   - Buttons: [SEND] [DELETE]
3. To copy TV remote: Point TV remote at TOBY → Tap **[LEARN]**
4. Code appears on screen: 0x20DF10EF NEC
5. Tap **** → Type name "TV_POWER" using virtual keyboard
6. To use: Point TOBY at TV → Select "TV_POWER" → Tap **[SEND]** → TV turns on
7. Tap **[< Back]** to return to main menu

### **9. Using SCFTOS - Phone Control**

1. Tap the **[SCFTOS]** button on TOBY
2. SCFTOS screen on TOBY shows:
   - Status: WAITING FOR PHONE
   - WiFi AP: TOBY-MK1
   - Password: toby12345
   - IP: 192.168.4.1
   - Instruction: 1. Connect to WiFi 2. Open in browser
   - Button: [DISABLE AP]
   - Clients: 0 | Uptime: 00:05:21
3. Connect phone to WiFi TOBY-MK1
4. Open browser on phone: 192.168.4.1
5. Control TOBY from phone: Start GPS, download files, run terminal
6. To close SCFTOS: Tap **[DISABLE AP]** on TOBY screen
7. Tap **[< Back]** to return to main menu

### **10. Updating Firmware - Bootloader**

1. Download `tobyos.bin` to root of SD card on your computer
2. Put SD card in TOBY
3. Tap the **[Bootloader]** button on main screen
4. Bootloader screen shows:
   - Current Version: V.1 PRO
   - Build: 2026.06.27
   - Update via: [SD CARD] tobyos.bin | [WiFi OTA] 192.168.4.1/update
   - WARNING:!! DO NOT POWER OFF DURING UPDATE!!
   - Button: [CHECK UPDATE]
5. Tap **[UPDATE VIA SD]**
6. Wait 60 seconds. **DO NOT POWER OFF TOBY**
7. Device reboots automatically with new TOBYOS
8. Tap **[< Back]** to return to main menu

### **11. Touch Calibration**

If touch is wrong or inaccurate:

1. Tap **[Config]** on main screen
2. Tap button **[CALIBRATE TOUCH]**
3. Calibration screen opens
4. Tap the 4 crosses that appear in the corners, one at a time
5. After tapping all 4 crosses, tap ****
6. TOBY reboots with calibrated touch

